  "texts": [
    "Table 1 ARHE benchmark breakdown Mutator Number Integer Literal Changer • 45 If Remover 24 String Literal Changer 63 Operator Changer • 40 Binary Operator Remover 24 Augmented Assignment Changer • 3 If Negator • 1 Reversible mutators are marked with •, irreversible mutators are marked with, and occasionally reversible mutators are marked with",
    "empty, lower-case, or upper-case; making the string literal an empty string is not reversible, but whether the lower-casing or upper-casing can be applied in the reverse to get the original code differs from problem to problem.",
    "The generation of empty strings is similar to the 'Empty returns Mutator' of PIT.",
    "'Operator Changer' will change pluses to minuses, along with similar operations, similarly to the 'Math Mutator' of PIT.",
    "'Binary Operator Remover' will remove a binary operator and only leave one of the operands, similarly to the 'Arithmetic Operator Deletion Mutator' of PIT."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}